To determine if a 3x3 grid is a valid Sudoku, you can check if the set of all elements in the grid contains the numbers 1 through 9 without any duplicates or extra numbers.

```python
def valid_sudoku_3x3(grid):
    flat_list = [item for sublist in grid for item in sublist]
    return sorted(flat_list) == list(range(1, 10))
```
